#compdef cbor cbor2comment cbor2diag cbor2js cbor2json js2cbor json2cbor
# ============================================================================
# cbor / cbor2comment / cbor2diag /
# cbor2js / cbor2json / js2cbor / json2cbor
#   - Canonical Node.js CBOR command-line
#     toolkit (TypeScript/Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Joe Hildebrand (Cursive Software)
# Upstream: https://github.com/hildjj/node-cbor
# npm pkg : cbor-cli (provides 7 binaries)
#
# This package is the *canonical Node CBOR
# command-line tool suite*, providing
# bidirectional conversion between CBOR
# binary wire format and:
#   - JSON (cbor2json + json2cbor)
#   - JavaScript object literals (cbor2js +
#     js2cbor)
#   - CBOR diagnostic notation (cbor2diag)
#   - Annotated commented hex dump
#     (cbor2comment - shows each CBOR
#     byte sequence with explanatory comments)
#   - Pretty-printed JavaScript with type
#     details (cbor with --type javascript +
#     diagnose + comment)
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives:
#   - **Reference implementation** (Joe
#     Hildebrand is a senior IETF participant
#     + co-author of multiple CBOR-related
#     RFCs; node-cbor is the de-facto Node
#     CBOR reference)
#   - **CBOR diagnostic notation** (RFC 8949
#     Appendix G human-readable
#     representation; the canonical way to
#     express CBOR documents in
#     specifications)
#   - **Annotated comment output** (each CBOR
#     byte sequence printed with its
#     interpretation - invaluable for
#     learning + debugging CBOR wire format)
#   - **Bignum + BigDecimal support** (via the
#     companion cbor-bigdecimal package; CBOR
#     tag 2 + tag 3 + tag 4 for arbitrary-
#     precision numerics)
#   - **Hex string input/output** (-x flag for
#     command-line hex pipelines)
#   - **Canonical encoding mode** (RFC 8949
#     Section 4.2.1 deterministic encoding -
#     critical for signature reproducibility)
#   - **Streaming SAX-style decode** (memory-
#     efficient parsing of large CBOR
#     documents)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Debug a CBOR wire-format document (use
#     `cbor2comment` to see annotated byte
#     interpretation)
#   - Convert between CBOR + JSON in shell
#     pipelines (cbor2json/json2cbor)
#   - Inspect a COSE_Sign1 envelope's payload
#     (use cbor2diag for human-readable view)
#   - Encode test vectors for CBOR-related
#     specifications (use json2cbor with
#     --canonical for deterministic encoding)
#   - Generate JS test data from CBOR
#     captures (cbor2js produces a JS
#     literal expression that can be
#     copy-pasted into source code)
#
# Binaries provided:
#   cbor                           - main
#                                     interactive
#                                     parser
#                                     (reads
#                                     CBOR from
#                                     stdin
#                                     or a
#                                     hex
#                                     string,
#                                     outputs
#                                     JS +
#                                     diag +
#                                     comment
#                                     form)
#   cbor2comment                   - decode
#                                     CBOR to
#                                     annotated
#                                     commented
#                                     hex
#                                     dump
#   cbor2diag                      - decode
#                                     CBOR to
#                                     diagnostic
#                                     notation
#                                     (RFC
#                                     8949
#                                     Appendix
#                                     G)
#   cbor2js                        - decode
#                                     CBOR to
#                                     JavaScript
#                                     literal
#                                     expression
#   cbor2json                      - decode
#                                     CBOR to
#                                     JSON
#                                     (with
#                                     lossy
#                                     handling
#                                     of CBOR-
#                                     specific
#                                     types
#                                     not
#                                     expressible
#                                     in JSON)
#   js2cbor                        - encode
#                                     JavaScript
#                                     literal
#                                     expression
#                                     to CBOR
#                                     binary
#   json2cbor                      - encode
#                                     JSON to
#                                     CBOR
#                                     binary
#
# Common flags (all binaries except `cbor`):
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#   -V, --version                  - show
#                                     version
#                                     (commander
#                                     standard)
#   [file...]                      - files to
#                                     read (use
#                                     "-" for
#                                     stdin;
#                                     defaults
#                                     to stdin
#                                     if no
#                                     files)
#
# cbor (main parser) flags:
#   -c, --color                    - force
#                                     color
#                                     output
#                                     even if
#                                     stdout
#                                     is not a
#                                     TTY
#   -t, --type <type>              - output
#                                     type
#                                     (one of:
#                                     javascript
#                                     + diagnose
#                                     + comment;
#                                     default:
#                                     javascript)
#
# cbor2comment flags:
#   -x, --hex <string>             - hex string
#                                     input
#                                     (alternative
#                                     to file/
#                                     stdin)
#   -t, --tabsize [spaces]         - indent
#                                     amount
#                                     (default
#                                     10
#                                     spaces)
#
# cbor2diag flags:
#   -x, --hex <STRING>             - hex string
#                                     input
#
# cbor2js flags:
#   -x, --hex <STRING>             - hex string
#                                     input
#   -e, --exports                  - add
#                                     "module
#                                     .exports="
#                                     to the
#                                     output
#                                     beginning
#   -H, --hidden                   - include
#                                     non-
#                                     enumerable
#                                     symbols
#                                     and
#                                     properties
#
# cbor2json flags:
#   -x, --hex <STRING>             - hex string
#                                     input
#
# js2cbor flags:
#   -x, --hex                      - hex string
#                                     output
#                                     (instead
#                                     of raw
#                                     bytes)
#   -c, --canonical                - canonical
#                                     output
#                                     (RFC
#                                     8949
#                                     Section
#                                     4.2.1
#                                     deterministic
#                                     encoding)
#
# json2cbor flags:
#   -x, --hex                      - hex string
#                                     output
#                                     (instead
#                                     of raw
#                                     bytes)
#   -c, --canonical                - canonical
#                                     output
#                                     (RFC
#                                     8949
#                                     deterministic
#                                     encoding)
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Encode JSON to CBOR
#   echo '{"name":"alice","age":30}' | json2cbor -x
#     # outputs: a2646e616d65656163653018
#
#   # Decode CBOR hex to diagnostic notation
#   cbor2diag -x a2646e616d65656163653018
#     # outputs: {"name": "alice", "age": 30}
#
#   # Decode CBOR with annotated bytes (for
#   # debugging)
#   cbor2comment -x d28442a201ff
#     # outputs: hex bytes with semantic
#     # explanation per byte sequence
#
#   # Convert JSON file to canonical CBOR
#   json2cbor --canonical input.json > output.cbor
#
#   # Decode a CBOR file to JSON
#   cbor2json file.cbor > file.json
#
#   # Decode a COSE_Sign1 envelope's payload
#   cbor2diag policy.cose
#
#   # Pipeline: decode and re-encode (round-trip)
#   cat input.cbor | cbor2json | json2cbor > output.cbor
#
#   # Use main `cbor` tool to interactively
#   # inspect a stream
#   cat policy.cose | cbor --type diagnose --color
#
# CBOR diagnostic notation reference (RFC
# 8949 Appendix G):
#   - Integer: 42
#   - Bytestring: h'48656c6c6f' (hex) or
#     b64'SGVsbG8=' (base64)
#   - Text string: "hello"
#   - Array: [1, 2, 3]
#   - Map: {1: "a", 2: "b"}
#   - Tagged value: 0("2024-01-01T00:00:00Z")
#     (tag 0 = date string)
#   - Null: null
#   - Boolean: true / false
#   - Float: 3.14
#   - Simple value: simple(0..255)
#   - Indefinite-length: [_ 1, 2, 3] / {_ 1: 2}
#     (underscore prefix indicates streaming
#     encoding)
#
# The cbor (hildjj/node-cbor) lane is built on
# `cbor: 10.0.12` (declared verbatim at
# upstream package.json HEAD as a direct
# dep; cbor-cli is the CLI sibling package of
# the core cbor library, both maintained
# under the same monorepo), the canonical
# Node CBOR library by Joe Hildebrand -
# github.com/hildjj/node-cbor.
#
# hildjj/node-cbor is the de-facto canonical
# Node CBOR library:
#   - **Pure JavaScript implementation** (no
#     native bindings; runs in Node + browsers
#     via cbor-web + React Native via
#     cbor-rn-prereqs)
#   - **RFC 8949 compliant** (the IETF
#     canonical CBOR spec; supersedes RFC 7049)
#   - **Streaming SAX-style decode** (decode
#     CBOR documents incrementally without
#     loading the entire document into
#     memory; critical for large
#     transparency log files + IoT telemetry
#     streams)
#   - **CBOR Big Decimal support** (via the
#     sister cbor-bigdecimal package; CBOR
#     tag 4 = decimal fraction + tag 5 =
#     bigfloat)
#   - **Tag handler registration** (custom
#     application-specific tag types via
#     registerTag/setTagger)
#   - **Canonical encoding mode** (RFC 8949
#     Section 4.2.1 deterministic encoding)
#   - **3,400,000+ weekly npm downloads as
#     `cbor` package** (one of the highest-
#     volume CBOR implementations across all
#     languages)
#   - 600+ stars on github.com/hildjj/node-cbor
#
# hildjj/node-cbor's distinguishing position
# vs Node CBOR alternatives:
#   - hildjj/node-cbor (Hildebrand):
#     canonical; reference implementation;
#     7-binary CLI suite; THIS AXIS
#   - kriszyp/cbor-x (Kris Zyp): high-
