#
# This is consistent with CBOR's origins
# at the IETF rather than at a specific
# company: IETF-originated specs typically
# have third-party implementations across
# all language lanes (similar to TLS - the
# rustls + Go std crypto/tls + Node tls
# implementations were all third-party).
#
# cbor-cli uses hildjj/node-cbor's core
# library for:
#   - CBOR document parsing (cbor2*
#     binaries use cbor.Decoder)
#   - CBOR document encoding (js2cbor +
#     json2cbor use cbor.Encoder)
#   - Commented output (cbor2comment uses
#     cbor.Commented stream)
#   - Diagnostic output (cbor2diag uses
#     cbor.Diagnose stream)
#   - BigDecimal handling (cbor +
#     json2cbor with bdec(cbor) integration)
#
# This is the canonical end-user CBOR
# tooling in the Node ecosystem - cbor-cli
# is what gets installed when developers
# need command-line CBOR conversion
# capability.
#
